@title Top-level pattern with no type signature

@code_type rust .rs

A test of a simple pattern which has no associated type annotation at the top level, and so, no type signature for the generated function. This should be an error.

--- no_type_signature.rs
#![feature(proc_macro_hygiene)]
extern crate ape;

use ape::arb_peg;

fn main() {
  arb_peg!{true}
}
---

--- no_type_signature.stderr
